name: War Memorial Park Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit trees in Coventry's premier park.
description: A selection of apple and pear trees available for public picking near the cafe area.

name: Sherbourne River Path Wild Garlic
short_description: Wild garlic along the river banks.
description: As Coventry is landlocked, coastal foraging is replaced by riverbank greens like Ramsons (wild garlic).

name: Coombe Abbey Hazelnuts
description: Hazel trees are abundant in the wilder wooded perimeter of the country park.

name: Incredible Edible Fargo Village
description: Planters around the independent hub containing rosemary, mint, and edible flowers.

name: Allesley Park Walled Garden
short_description: Historic fruit trees in a walled setting.
description: Community-run orchard with heavy-cropping apple trees open to the public.

name: Canley Ford Blackberries
short_description: Abundant brambles in a nature reserve.
description: Large crops of blackberries line the paths through the meadows and wooded edges.

name: Lake View Park Elder
description: Multiple elder trees grow along the boundary hedgerows of the park.

name: Coventry Canal Basin Herbs
short_description: Planters along the historic canal side.
description: Community planters at the basin often contain chives, parsley, and thyme.

name: Tile Hill Wood Chestnuts
description: Scattered sweet chestnut trees are found in this historic woodland site.

name: Stoke Floods Sloes
short_description: Blackthorn bushes near the nature reserve.
description: Excellent spot for picking sloes for gin in the late autumn months.

name: Longford Park Fruit Trail
description: Part of a green corridor featuring newly planted and established fruit trees.

name: Gosford Green Elderberries
description: Central urban green space with several large elder bushes near the periphery.

name: Quinton Park Walnuts
description: Mature walnut trees can be found around the lake area in this suburban park.

name: Incredible Edible Charterhouse
short_description: Herb gardens near the historic priory.
description: Community planters focusing on culinary herbs used since medieval times.

name: Tocil Wood Wild Garlic
short_description: Woodland garlic patches near the university.
description: Dense patches of wild garlic grow in the damp soils of this historic wood.
